---
import PublicPagesLayout from '@layouts/PublicPagesLayout.astro';
---

<PublicPagesLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Bitcoin API"
  description="Terms of Service for using the Bitcoin API platform.">
  <main class="py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#565d6d]">Last updated: April 12, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-[#565d6d] leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing or using the Bitcoin API service ("Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, you may not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p>
            Bitcoin API provides a RESTful API for accessing Bitcoin market data, blockchain information, and related services. We reserve the right to modify, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Service at any time.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">3. API Keys & Account Security</h2>
          <p>
            You are responsible for keeping your API keys confidential. Any activity that occurs under your account is your responsibility. Notify us immediately if you suspect unauthorized use of your credentials.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">4. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p class="mb-3">You agree not to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Use the Service for any unlawful purpose</li>
            <li>Attempt to reverse-engineer or compromise the Service</li>
            <li>Exceed published rate limits or circumvent usage restrictions</li>
            <li>Resell or redistribute API data without permission</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">5. Rate Limits & Fair Use</h2>
          <p>
            Each plan has defined rate limits. We may throttle or suspend access if usage patterns negatively affect the Service for other users.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">6. Data Accuracy</h2>
          <p>
            We strive to provide accurate and up-to-date data but make no guarantees regarding completeness or accuracy. The Service should not be used as the sole basis for financial decisions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Bitcoin API shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">8. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            We may suspend or terminate your access at any time for violation of these terms. You may also stop using the Service at any time by deleting your account.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">9. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use of the Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#171a1f] mb-3">10. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about these terms, please contact us at
            <a href="mailto:support@bitcoin-api.dev" class="text-[#0983FD] hover:underline">support@bitcoin-api.dev</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</PublicPagesLayout>
